ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 293}, {\"ngram\": \"around 100 teenage boys\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 322}, {\"ngram\": \"young men\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 336}, {\"ngram\": \"their tents\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 387}, {\"ngram\": \"belongings\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris police said the operation was carried out for security reasons, notably because the camp was near schools.\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 405, \"end\": 410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.720417121229587e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the operation\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"security reasons\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"the camp\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 499}, {\"ngram\": \"schools\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris-region officials told the men - many of them minors and in the process of seeking residency papers - that they could be housed temporarily for three weeks in the Loire-region town of Angers if they wished.\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 730, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paris-region officials\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 541}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 554}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 595}, {\"ngram\": \"residency papers\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 623}, {\"ngram\": \"three weeks\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 679}, {\"ngram\": \"the Loire-region town\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 704}, {\"ngram\": \"Angers\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A bus was waiting in a nearby street to take them first to aParis-region transit center.\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A bus\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"a nearby street\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"aParis-region transit center\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only two or three men boarded the bus.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Only two or three men\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 842}, {\"ngram\": \"the bus\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 858}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of the others walked away, carrying their belongings.\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the others\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"their belongings\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 917}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some said they feared being left isolated and abandoned in Angers, 250 kilometers (150 miles) southwest ofthe French capital, once the three weeks of temporary accommodation run out.\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Angers\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"250 kilometers\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1000}, {\"ngram\": \"150 miles\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1011}, {\"ngram\": \"southwest ofthe French capital\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1043}, {\"ngram\": \"once the three weeks\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"temporary accommodation\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1092}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those evicted from camps and squats are liable to set up makeshift settlements elsewhere inthe French capitaland be cleared out again, says a campaign group that has been sounding the alarm about the Olympics' impact on marginalized people.\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1343, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"camps\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"squats\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"makeshift settlements\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1181}, {\"ngram\": \"inthe French capitaland\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"a campaign group\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1259}, {\"ngram\": \"the alarm\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics' impact\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1319}, {\"ngram\": \"marginalized people\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1342}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTOS: Ahead of the Paris Olympics, police clear a migrant camp near City Hall \\\"It's a never-ending cycle,\\\" said Antoine de Clerck, a spokesman for the Revers de la M\\u00e9daille group, which translates as \\\"the other side of the medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1471, \"end\": 1477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\", \"score\": 0.9999999999677129, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clerck\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Alexander_Clerck\"}, {\"begin\": 1499, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"score\": 0.9999999975407263, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Revers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTOS\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"a migrant camp\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"City Hall\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"a never-ending cycle\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"a spokesman\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"the other side\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We call it 'nettoyage social,' or social cleansing, as there is no proper solution(s) that are proposed to the people,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"social cleansing\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1631}, {\"ngram\": \"no proper solution(s\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1665}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1698}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He alleged that people are being swept aside to make \\\"room for the beautifulParispostcard.\\\"\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1802, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"room\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"the beautifulParispostcard\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1800}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a written order that announced Tuesday's clear-out in advance, Paris police chief Laurent Nunez said the makeshift camp was made up of more than 80 tents and was blocking pavements.\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1870, \"end\": 1875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.720417121229587e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a written order\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1822}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday's clear-out\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"advance\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"the makeshift camp\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 80 tents\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"pavements\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 1987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The order also noted that the camp was near public buildings, including a church and City Hall, where security has been increased because France is on heightened alert against possible terrorism threats.\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2127, \"end\": 2133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6559915229476553, \"rank\": 0.3567063197890549, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The order\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1998}, {\"ngram\": \"the ca